<subSubSection id="C31A1DA0FFECFFFB9D1558B3FC87C37C" lastPageId="55" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFECFFFA9D1558B3FE3DC593" blockId="54.[264,799,1164,1225]" box="[264,426,1199,1225]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<figureCitation id="133B52AEFFECFFFA9D1558B3FE3DC593" box="[264,426,1199,1225]" captionStart="FIGURES 205­209" captionStartId="89.[264,382,1832,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-43@89.[213,1336,288,1377]" captionTargetPageId="89" captionText="FIGURES 205­209. Male terminalia of Ommatius segouensis, sp. n. 205­207. Lateral, dorsal and ventral views; 208. Gonostylus; 209. Aedeagus, lateral view. sp. n." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5080307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5080307/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs. 205­209</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFECFFFA9D1558E3FBE0C433" blockId="54.[264,1323,1279,1865]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Male. As 
<taxonomicName id="4C0035A8FFECFFFA9D9F58E3FD9CC442" authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[386,523,1279,1304]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinus">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFECFFFA9D9F58E3FD9CC442" box="[386,523,1279,1304]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">O. pectinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except as follows. Length, body 9.3­10.0 mm; wing 7.0­ 
<quantity id="4CF8E3CEFFECFFFA98DB58E3FAB0C443" box="[1222,1319,1279,1305]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.3" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="7.3">7.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B9749239FFECFFFA9D15593BFED0C41A" box="[264,327,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Head</emphasis>
: FHWR 1.0:5.2­1.0:6.0. Mystax with 2­3 yellow bristles; 4 thin, brown bristles present. Pedicel with 1 unusually long yellow seta, apex beyond flagellum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFECFFFA9D25596BFAB3C4E3" blockId="54.[264,1323,1279,1865]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFECFFFA9D25596BFE1BC4CA" box="[312,396,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Thorax</emphasis>
: Mesonotum yellowish­brown tomentose anteriorly, otherwise yellowish­gray to gray; setae mostly yellow, sparse brown setae present between dorsocentrals posteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFECFFFA9D2559DBFD32C4BB" blockId="54.[264,1323,1279,1865]" box="[312,677,1479,1505]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFECFFFA9D2559DBFEE3C4BA" box="[312,372,1479,1504]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Wing</emphasis>
: As 
<taxonomicName id="4C0035A8FFECFFFA9DB659DBFDA7C4BA" authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[427,560,1479,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinus">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFECFFFA9DB659DBFDA7C4BA" box="[427,560,1479,1504]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">O. pectinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="133B52AEFFECFFFA9E5C59DBFD00C4BB" box="[577,663,1479,1505]" captionStart="FIGURES 11­20" captionStartId="64.[264,382,1737,1761]" captionTargetBox="[281,1307,320,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-93@64.[246,1324,302,1632]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURES 11­20. Right wing of male Ommatius (Pygommatius) spp. 11. O. imaginus, sp. n..; 12. O. limbus, sp. n..; 13. O. litoreus sp. n.; 14. O. lulua, sp. n.; 15. O. magnipes, sp. n.; 16. O. ornatipes Engel; 17. O. pectinus sp. n.; 18. O. porticus, sp. n.; 19. O. renudus, sp. n.; 20. O. strigiatus, sp. n." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5019047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5019047/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFECFFFA9D2559F3FCF2C703" blockId="54.[264,1323,1279,1865]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFECFFFA9D2559F3FEF3C752" box="[312,356,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Leg</emphasis>
: Fore femur (see 
<taxonomicName id="4C0035A8FFECFFFA9E2659F3FD20C752" authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[571,695,1519,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grossus">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFECFFFA9E2659F3FD20C752" box="[571,695,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">O. grossus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation id="133B52AEFFECFFFA9ED859F3FC8DC753" box="[709,794,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 21­28" captionStartId="65.[264,382,1754,1778]" captionTargetBox="[277,1313,348,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-98@65.[242,1321,324,1693]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 21­28. Right wing of male Ommatius (Pygommatius) spp. 21. O. talus, sp. n.; 22. O. vultus, sp. n.; 23­28. Right fore femur of male Ommatius (Pygommatius) spp. showing arrangement of anteroventral bristles. 23. O. brevicornis Curran; 24. O. grossus, sp. n.; 25. O. limbus, sp. n.; 26. O. litoreus, sp. n.; 27. O. strigiatus, sp. n..; 28. O. vultus, sp. n." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5019049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5019049/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) with a row of ventral bristles. Middle femur with 5 long, stout posteroventral bristles. FHWLR 1.0:6.7­1.0:7.1. Fore and middle tarsi laterally with 10 and 4 yellow bristles, respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFECFFFA9D255A7BFBC5C7DB" blockId="54.[264,1323,1279,1865]" box="[312,1106,1639,1665]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFECFFFA9D255A7BFE31C7DA" box="[312,422,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Sternites 2­5 with numerous, erect, stout, yellow bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFECFFFA9D255A93FB73C67B" blockId="54.[264,1323,1279,1865]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFECFFFA9D255A93FE2FC7F2" box="[312,440,1679,1704]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133B52AEFFECFFFA9DDA5A93FDE6C7F3" box="[455,625,1679,1705]" captionStart="FIGURES 205­209" captionStartId="89.[264,382,1832,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-43@89.[213,1336,288,1377]" captionTargetPageId="89" captionText="FIGURES 205­209. Male terminalia of Ommatius segouensis, sp. n. 205­207. Lateral, dorsal and ventral views; 208. Gonostylus; 209. Aedeagus, lateral view. sp. n." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5080307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5080307/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs. 205­209</figureCitation>
): Ventral lamella as 
<taxonomicName id="4C0035A8FFECFFFA9F405A93FC29C7F2" authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[861,958,1679,1704]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinus">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFECFFFA9F405A93FC29C7F2" box="[861,958,1679,1704]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">pectinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except comb­like setae longer, thicker. Epandrium 3 branched; dorsal process short, concealed along inner surface of median branch; median branch wide with pointed apex; ventral branch narrow, forked apically. Hypandrium anteriorly with flat tuft of fused bristles, leaf­like in ventral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFECFFFA9D255B33FD8FC613" blockId="54.[264,1323,1279,1865]" box="[312,536,1839,1865]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
