<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFEDFFFB9D255D70FB42C0DC" blockId="55.[264,1322,283,550]" box="[312,1237,364,390]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Etymology. Latin, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0035A8FFEDFFFB9E0E5D70FD05C0DF" authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[531,658,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="segouensis">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFEDFFFB9E0E5D70FD05C0DF" box="[531,658,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">segouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of or pertaining to Segòu, 
<collectingCountry id="F3170EBBFFEDFFFB9FC85D70FB98C0DC" box="[981,1039,364,390]" name="Serbia" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Mali</collectingCountry>
, its 
<typeStatus id="54BBF089FFEDFFFB98235D70FBE7C0DC" box="[1086,1136,364,390]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFEDFFFB9D255D88FC21C0F4" blockId="55.[264,1322,283,550]" box="[312,950,404,430]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Distribution. Known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54BBF089FFEDFFFB9EC45D88FC9CC0F4" box="[729,779,404,430]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<collectingCountry id="F3170EBBFFEDFFFB9F6A5D88FC25C0F4" box="[887,946,404,430]" name="Serbia" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Mali</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFEDFFFB9D255DA0FC87C37C" blockId="55.[264,1322,283,550]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0035A8FFEDFFFB9DB35DA0FD3AC08F" box="[430,685,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seqouensis">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFEDFFFB9DB35DA0FD3AC08F" box="[430,685,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ommatius seqouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0035A8FFEDFFFB9F595DA0FC5EC08F" authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[836,969,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinus">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFEDFFFB9F595DA0FC5EC08F" box="[836,969,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">O. pectinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from congeners by the characters in the key, the smaller body, long yellow posteroventral bristles on the middle femur, and erect bristles on sternites 2­5.
</paragraph>
